# Component Library

Local MDSvX component guidance for Pi Discord Threads.

pi-notes ships standard components and auto-imports project-local Svelte components from `.brain/components/**/*.svelte` when they are used in `.svx` pages.

## Rules

- Keep `.svx` as the narrative shell.
- Put large structured data in `.brain/data/**`.
- Put reusable renderers in `.brain/components/**`.
- Prefer focused components over boolean prop soup.
- Show provenance, freshness, privacy, and action side effects when a component reads data or triggers work.

## Useful standard components

- `<NoteCallout tone="info" title="Note">...</NoteCallout>`
- `<StatusPill label="active" tone="success" />`
- `<SourceReference path="src/file.ts" label="Source" />`
- `<ReviewReceipt batchId="..." status="handled" />`
- `<DiagramFrame src="/diagrams/example.svg" source="docs/diagrams/example" renderer="mermaid" />`

## Project components

Create project-specific components in `.brain/components/` only when a shape repeats or depends on structured data.

## Summary Component Kit direction

The active direction is captured in [Session Memory and Summary Components](../projects/session-memory-summary-components.svx): build a shadcn-style copy-in library for useful MDSvX summary pages, starting from the `wzrrd` `joel/tufte-mdsvx` Tufte notes template.

Use these names consistently:

- **Project Memory Portal** — a stable tailnet SvelteKit/MDSvX site URL for project Brain plus workstream/session/turn/tool-call drilldown.
- **Session Memory Note** — a real `.brain/**/*.svx` page for one Discord/Pi workstream inside the broader portal.
- **Brain Context Strip** — a compact HUD/final-summary link set for recent or relevant Brain notes.
- **Summary Component Kit** — source-copyable MDSvX components for memory, receipts, decisions, risks, timelines, and next actions.
- **Agent Component Doctrine** — prompt/docs rules for how agents create and extend the component system.

Canonical home for reusable summary components is the `wzrrd` template/component registry, but the durable local Brain portal likely belongs in `joelhooks/pi-notes` because it already owns the Document Host, `.brain` rendering, and Session Bridge. Dogfood the first visible slice in `pi-discord-threads`, especially the running HUD Brain Context Strip, terminal Tweet-Sized Memory Card, and Session Memory Note/Project Memory Portal links.

Do not make this an opaque package. Prefer copyable source, recipes, data contracts, and small focused components that can graduate between local Brain components and the `wzrrd` registry without hiding the source.
